description: An first Telegram Userbot with multi Clients for Spamming or Mass.

API_ID.description: Your API ID from my.telegram.org. Required for Pyrogram client initialization.

API_HASH.description: Your API Hash from my.telegram.org. Required for Pyrogram client initialization.

SUDO_USERS.description: Space-separated list of user IDs who will have sudo access to the bot. Example: '123456789 987654321'.

OWNER_ID.description: The user ID of the bot owner. This user will have full control.

MONGO_URL.description: MongoDB connection URI. Obtain this from MongoDB Atlas or a similar service. Example: 'mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database?retryWrites=true&w=majority'.

BOT_TOKEN.description: Your bot token from @BotFather. Required for bot functionality.

ALIVE_PIC.description: URL of an image to be used as the 'alive' picture for the bot. Example: 'https://example.com/image.jpg'.

ALIVE_TEXT.description: Custom text to be displayed with the 'alive' picture. Leave empty for default.

PM_LOGGER.description: Chat ID of a private message logger group/channel. Leave empty if not needed.

LOG_GROUP.description: Chat ID of a group/channel for logging bot activities. Leave empty if not needed.

GIT_TOKEN.description: Personal access token for Git (e.g., GitHub). Required for repository operations. Leave empty if not needed.

REPO_URL.description: URL of the Git repository. Default is 'https://github.com'.

BRANCH.description: The branch of the repository to use. Default is 'master'. Do not change unless you know what you are doing.

STRING_SESSION1.description: Telethon session string for the first user account. Generate using the provided script or method.

STRING_SESSION2.description: Telethon session string for the second user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION3.description: Telethon session string for the third user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION4.description: Telethon session string for the fourth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION5.description: Telethon session string for the fifth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION6.description: Telethon session string for the sixth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION7.description: Telethon session string for the seventh user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION8.description: Telethon session string for the eighth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION9.description: Telethon session string for the ninth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.

STRING_SESSION10.description: Telethon session string for the tenth user account. Leave empty if not using multiple accounts.
